  <p align="left"><strong>Welcome to the last update of the Year and the Decade.</strong></p>
  <p align="left"><strong>Glen&rsquo;s Leadership New Zealand experience</strong></p>
  <p align="left"> I have just completed being part of the Leadership New Zealand programme for 2010. What an incredible and insightful programme. Thirty participants, from around the country, from all sectors: Business, Government, Council, and Community on a leadership journey. We began in February and graduated at the end of November. Each month we were together for two to three day retreats where we delved into issues like: a civil society, our people, 21st century governance, New Zealand on the world stage, leadership and innovation, the media &hellip;.. I've come away from this rather flash experience with a new confidence around the skills and abilities I have to offer, plus realising that to be someone of influence doesn't mean you need to be rich and powerful. Meeting people like Sir Paul Reeves, Sir Tipene O'Regan, Pat Snedden and Debbie and Ngahau Davis was humbling and exciting. From here I'm challenged to be more at ease with my skills base, having a better perspective and vision for our future. <a href="http://www.leadershipnz.co.nz">www.leadershipnz.co.nz</a></p>
  <p align="left"> 
          Thanks so much to Incedo for your generous support of me while I've been on the programme. 
        </p>
  <p align="left">Please feel free to contact me if you would like to find out more about my experience.            </p>
  <p align="left">&nbsp;</p>
  <p align="left">Glen </p>
